Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Place prepared chicken in the bottom of a 9x13 inch casserole dish. Cover the chicken with sliced eggs. Bring soup and broth to a boil and pour over the chicken and eggs. In a bowl, combine the flour, buttermilk and melted butter. Mix and pour over the chicken. Bake in the preheated oven for 45 minutes.